cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.DB, cs.CR 

This paper focuses on generating synthetic medical data using generative adversarial networks, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of summary statistics to transform the data and the need for stratification by covariates suggest a potential application in database systems (cs.DB) and computational epidemiology (cs.CR). Finally, the paper also discusses the challenges of extending time series modeling methods to medical event data, which could be relevant to the category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE).
